{
  "stem": "14060.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That was some sort of providence that communities shouldn't split.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But the bottom line, what I'm trying to say, is that my father was the head of the chevra kadisha, which is the burial society.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And it's interesting to note, for those who didn't live in that part of the world, or even some who did but who were maybe too young to know, or the too old ones are not around, it was a by government authorized autonomous communities, separately the Orthodox and the Neolog communities.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And the existence was basically through a charter, a government charter.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "In Hungary, in my time certainly, every individual whether Jew or non-Jew, had to belong to a religious community.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "If they happened to be-- which was basically ostracized, say they are non-believers, they also had what they called Unitarian community.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "The majority of Hungary was Catholic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "That was the mainstream.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "There were some Protestants in great minority and Jews also in relative minority.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I mean, as I think I mentioned, in our town of 60,000 people, there were 1,800 Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We certainly lived a very modern, Westernized life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Shtetls I never seen in my life until I got to Israel and I've seen it in the [INAUDIBLE] on videos.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And generally, I would say that we-- I can't say that I had a cultural shock after the war having left from there, because of the general lifestyle which we had.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you mean personally?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Behaviorwise, I was known as a little bit of a terror.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was always inclined to do work.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was told that-- I had an older brother, who was six years older by name of Erwin, who was a very gentle boy, who was tremendously good in academic field.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
